snippet: Omar Abdel Hamid El-Hussein is remembered as a young man of intelligence who harbored a growing rage against Danish society.
abstract: Omar Abdel Hamid el-Hussein, Danish man who died in battle with police following two suspected shootings in Copenhagen, does not fit typical profile of Islamic fundamentalist; Hussein, who belonged to gang that identified more with outsiderism than religion, is instead described as intelligent and angry young man who harbored growing rage against Denmark's liberal society.

byline.original: By ANDREW HIGGINS and MELISSA EDDY

lead_paragraph: Omar Abdel Hamid El-Hussein is remembered as a young man of intelligence who harbored a growing rage against Danish society.

headline.main: Anger of Suspect in Danish Killings Is Seen as Only Loosely Tied to Islam
headline.print_headline: Anger of Suspect in Danish Killings Is Seen as Only Loosely Tied to Islam
